Barrett, maybe you could tell us more about how to make it a Reactive thing to respond

00:08:05.279 --> 00:08:11.079
to versus, you know, like in the filtering thing, I didn't make it Reactive.

00:08:11.079 --> 00:08:12.079
Yes.

00:08:12.679 --> 00:08:18.480
In Python, your outputs are objects at the end, which is great.

00:08:18.480 --> 00:08:23.519
We can use these objects, and we've added on these extra methods that are explained

00:08:23.519 --> 00:08:29.839
in that 0.9.0 blog post where we're trying to empower the renderer to have a little bit

00:08:29.839 --> 00:08:36.479
more context, and so we've added methods like .data or .dataview of what the user is looking

00:08:36.479 --> 00:08:42.119
at, and those functions or values are Reactive.

00:08:42.119 --> 00:08:45.799
So if you use them in a Reactive setting, they'll automatically trigger with updates

00:08:45.799 --> 00:08:52.000
whenever, like, things happen upstream, which is great.

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:57.719
And there's other things in there, like cell selection, sort, and filter.

00:08:57.719 --> 00:09:03.200
You can get all of that information reactively, given what the user is looking at.

